# Line endings (Unix for gradlew, CRLF for the Windows launcher)
gradlew text eol=lf
gradlew.bat text eol=crlf
gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar binary

# --- Linguist language detection ---
# KordX is a Kotlin / Jetpack Compose Android app. The vendored taglib
# C++ library (and the utfcpp 3rd-party helper inside it) under
# `metaphony/src/main/cpp/` make the C++ count larger than the Kotlin
# count, which causes the repo card to show "C++" as the primary
# language. Mark the vendored native code and the generated C++ build
# directory as vendored so GitHub surfaces Kotlin (the language KordX
# is actually written in) as primary.
metaphony/src/main/cpp/**        linguist-vendored
metaphony/.cxx/**                linguist-generated
**/.cxx/**                       linguist-generated
**/build/generated/**            linguist-generated
